Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @sweet potato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.

Toss sweet potato on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-22%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet after 11 minutes).

While sweet potato roasts, using a #rolling pin{} or heavy-bottomed pan, crush peppercorns inside packet of @bold & savory steak spice{1%tbsp}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with 1 1/2 tsp Steak Spice (all for 4 servings), a big pinch of salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add chicken and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{6-8%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken for pork. Cook until browned and cooked through, 6-8 minutes per side.

Once sweet potato has roasted ~{11%minutes}, remove sheet from oven. Carefully toss sweet potato; add chicken to empty side of baking sheet.

Return to top rack until chicken is cooked through and sweet potato is browned and tender, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

> Skip the resting step for chicken!

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a medium #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and half the garlic (you'll use the rest in the next step); cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @Israeli couscous{5%ounce} and stir to coat. Stir in @water{1 1/2%cups} (about 2¼ cups for 4 servings), @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Drain any excess liquid if necessary. Season with salt and pepper if desired. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While couscous cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add remaining garlic and cook, stirring often, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @water{1/4%cup} (about 1/3 cup for 4 servings), @mushroom stock concentrate{1}, and @cream cheese{2%tbsp}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cream cheese melts and sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

Stir roasted sweet potato into pot with couscous.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide couscous and chicken between plates. Spoon pan sauce over chicken. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Thinly slice pork crosswise in original recipe. Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.